Is Pingdom Effectively Dead?
text:
Is Pingdom effectively dead/abandoned/stale/whatever? Seems slow and buggy and support is unresponsive.

I guess I already know the answer. So any recommendations for a similar product that will monitor endpoints as well as do simple "go to that URL, click the link, check for text" kind of scenarios? Doesn't have to be free. In fact, I would prefer to pay for it.

Thx!

Ask HN: What's Stopping You from Blogging?
text:
I know it's fallen out of favor lately but I still enjoying blogging. I've been blogging since 2007 and I'm interested in encouraging others.

I started writing, publicly but to myself, primarily so I could remember how to do technical processes that I didn't repeat very often.

If you've ever considered blogging but haven't started what's stopping you?
